  "stem": "<p>Lily made <math alttext=\"36\"><mn>36</mn>\n</math> cups of jam. Lily then filled <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> small containers and <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math> large containers with all the jam she made. The equation <math alttext=\"4 x plus 6 y equals 36\"><mrow>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mn>4</mn>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mn>6</mn>\n\t\t\t<mi>y</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t</mrow>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mn>36</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math> represents this situation. Which is the best interpretation of <math alttext=\"6 y\"><mrow>\n\t<mn>6</mn>\n\t<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math> in this context?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
