  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 x plus 6 y equals 36\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math> represents the situation where Lily filled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> small containers and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> large containers with all the jam she made, which was <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"36\"><mn>36</mn></math> cups. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 y\"><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> represents the total number of cups of jam in the large containers.</span></p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. The number of large containers Lily filled is represented by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math>, not&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 y\"><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice B is incorrect. The number of small containers Lily filled is represented by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math>, not&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 y\"><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect. The total number of cups of jam in the small containers is represented by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 x\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></math>, not&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 y\"><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>",
